Available in 9mm, and .40 S&W, the SP2022 can easily be converted from a Double-Action/Single-Action to a Double-Action Only configuration through a unique integral fire control unit. It also features the SIG SAUER four-point safety system. The SIG SAUER polymer framed pistols has earned an enviable reputation and proven track record of reliable performance in the hands of law enforcement professionals. In December of 2004 the U.S. Army Tank-automotive and Armaments Command at the Rock Island Arsenal awarded SIG SAUER a contract for 5,000 SIG SAUER SP2022 pistols chambered in 9mm.

.223 die set WITH the factory crimp die

case lube

title: For Sale:  Weatherby Mark V Accumark .30-378
postcontent:
I have a Weatherby Mark V Accumark chambered in .30-378 Weatherby Magnum for sale.

The rifle is in almost new condition.  There are a few very minor blemishes, mostly on the scope, from being carried in brushy terrain.  You'll have to look closely to see them but a blemish is a blemish.  It is about as lightly used gun as your likely to find though.  I haven't carried this rifle in the field in over ten years.  

I just don't hunt the type of terrain where I can see 200 yards much less shoot beyond that so lugging around a twelve pound rifle that blows hat sized holes through deer at typically bow shot range proved not to make a lot of sense to me.  

This rifle is an absolute blast to shoot!  Pun intended.  With the muzzle break on the recoil is in the .270 Winchester range.  Even girls can shoot it.  The concussion from the muzzle blast can be felt by bystanders 20 feet away so it's always a crowd favorite and the biggest conversation piece at the range.  You can also prank the "tough guys" by taking the muzzle break off.  This rifle slams into your shoulder like a 416 Rigby without the muzzle break on.   

The rifle comes with a Leupold Vari-X III 3.5-10X50 scope, padded thumbhole sling, and comes with reloading components.  I have the shell holder, dies, two pounds of unopened powder, a couple hundred controlled expansion bullets, and 38 empty cases with 2 loaded rounds of ammo.

I purchased this rifle brand new in 1997!  Serial # under 600 for the Accumark production run.  This rifle has some collectable value right now and will have serious collectable value in the future.  I was on a waiting list several months for Weatherby to manufacture my rifle.

The Accumark in .30-378 is still the same today as it was when introduced in 1997.  It features the same 28" fluted barrel with muzzle break and the same aluminum bedded synthetic stock.  The only thing a new rifle has is a much higher serial number and a much higher price.

The Weatherby Accumark currently retails for $2100 and the scope costed $600 out the door.  As a general rule used late model guns in excellent condition sell for about half of retail.

I'm asking $1000 for the rifle alone or $1300 for the rifle, scope, sling combo.  I'll toss about $400 worth of reloading components into the deal. 

Contact Brian at:  REDACTED to scedual an appointment.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson M&P 15 300 aac Blackout
postcontent:
Advanced Armament Corp. 300 AAC Blackout (300BLK). This system was developed to launch 30 caliber projectiles from the AR platform without a reduction in magazine capacity and compatible with the standard bolt. 

Full power 115-125 grain ammunition matches the ballistics of the 7.62x39mm AK, and eclipses 5.56mm with much higher-mass projectiles for a more dramatic effect on the target. Or choose subsonic cartridges for optimal use with a sound suppressor - 220 grain Sierra OTM (open-tip match) bullets vastly outperforms a 9mm MP5-SD in penetration and long range accuracy. 

Ammo and brass prices are low - Remington 115 grain UMC ammo is $12.99 a box MSRP - and it is not bare bones. It has waterproofed primers, crimped and cannelured open-tip match bullets, and a low-drag design.

At 300 meters, 300 BLK has 16.7% more energy than 7.62x39mm. Max effective range, using M4 military standards for hit probability, is 440 meters for a 9 inch barrel, and 460 meters for a 16 inch barrel. 300 BLK from a 9 inch barrel has the same energy at the muzzle as a 14.5 inch barrel M4, and about 5% more energy at 440 meters - even though the barrel is much shorter.

For hunting - think of it as like a 30-30 but from an AR. After you are done, you can remove your 5-round magazine and put in a 30 for plinking or home defense. For ammo, Remington has you covered with the Premiere AccuTip 125 grain. Want industry-wide support? Over 60 companies have already announced or sell products.

Due to the high efficiency of the cartridge, less powder is used than 5.56mm, which results in a rifle that is a comfortable to shoot - even with a short barrel. 

Reloading dies available from Forster products, Reamers and headspace guages available from Pacific Tool and Gauge.

3 boxes of Ammo Included

title: For Sale:  INTERESTED IN AMMO GROUP BUY ON CONTAINER OF AMMO FROM CANADA?
postcontent: Here is the deal. I have an FFL dealer I buy from, he is older and has trouble hearing. 90 Yr. WWII Marine Veteran. While looking for wholesale sources for .223/556 and 7.62X39 for him (me) I discovered a company in Canada that gets large quantities of surplus and other ammo. The catch is that they mostly do not ship to the USA except for VERY large amounts. They supply to midway to give you an idea. I felt very comfortable with the guy I spoke with on the phone. He said that basically to do a deal you have to submit a special import/export hazardous materials thing. The fee for that application is around $300 and it takes 3-6 weeks to be approved or not. So, I got this crazy idea that maybe normal people and even some smaller dealers could band together and make a large purchase like this. I am willing to facilitate and organize this. Why? Because the price of ammo is pissing me off, and I fear ammo is where the gun hating commies may try to hit us the hardest. So, this is an initial broadcast just to see if there is ANY interested in doing something like this. I have no idea how I would be able to prove to anyone its legitimate other than providing the info of my gunsmith, but really that will only prove he is a legitimate FFL; in reality I would be the one handling it. I have an email to my contact there in Canada, to narrow down more just exactly HOW big we are talking, to make something like this happen. Obviously, with the fees involved, we would have to make it worth while so we could all get good per round prices. That may be as much as a 1/2 to whole container. If you are in a hurry, this is not for you. If you are planning to spend less than $1000 on this, its not for you. Im just guessing with those numbers, but I am confident the amount we are talking about will be significant. As I get people who show interest I will create a facebook page, google cirlce, or maybe just a plain old email list. UPDATE: 1/8 FFL has agreed to help me out with this by using his FFL on the application.

HK USP Compact 45 
(Heckler & Koch GmbH of Oberndorf, Germany)

USP Compacts are smaller and lighter than large frame USPs. The reduction in trigger reach and grip circumference increases concealability and enhances shooting ergonomics. Unlike some subcompact semiautomatic pistols that use a difficult to shoot "two-finger grip" frame, the USP Compact uses a narrow, full-hand grip frame with a choice of interchangeable extended or flush-fitting magazine floorplates. This makes the pistol easy to shoot without sacrificing concealability.

Like their large frame predecessors, USP Compacts are designed with the demanding needs of the law enforcement and military shooters in mind. Using a modified linkless Browning-type action, the USP Compact is built to take the punishment of high-energy +P loads.

To reduce the length of the slide and barrel on the USP Compact, the mechanical recoil reduction system found on large frame USPs has been replaced by a specially designed flat compression spring contained in the captive recoil spring assembly by a polymer absorber bushing. Service life is still engineered to exceed 20,000 rounds.

title: For Sale:  Scam Alert... Don't be fooled
postcontent: Guy selling a polytech ak, guy selling a kimber stainless 45, and another one selling ar 15 mags. These guys are advertising at a given price. Waiting to see how much interest in their item they get. Then, they keep increasing the price every couple days until the top price is still getting attention. They will answer emails and agree to meet you and give a firm price but when the time and place come to meet they will not answer email or text. So buyer beware, these clowns are on the loose again. If they want an auction they should use gunbroker not this classified site.
